<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Herbert</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-27"><hi rend="italic">September 27,
                                    1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to send you a copy of a
                            note under date of August 13 which I have received from the German
                            chargé in this city, relative to a proposed fee of $5, which it is
                            understood the chief justice of Samoa intends to impose for the
                            registration of every separate title to land. I also inclose a copy of
                            my reply, and should be glad to be informed of the opinion of Her
                            Majesty’s Government upon this subject.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>